post_text:
The 3rd Annual "Musical Notes & Rootbeer Floats" music student talent showcase will be presented in the middle school theater on Tuesday, November 13 at 7:00 p.m. Admission is FREE! A rootbeer float fundraiser will follow immediately in the middle school commons. Freewill donation of $3-5 per float is suggested. Floats will be sponsored and served by Dacotah Bank.
MPHS music students will present a variety of popular tunes by Imagine Dragons, Adele, Billy Joel, rhe Beatles, Stevie Wonder, Barbara Streisand, and more! Bring the whole family for a fun hour of swingin' songs and sweet treats!

What did the ocean say to the beach? Nothing! It just waved!

What did one eye say to the other eye? Don't look now, but something between us smells!

Attention San Antonio music trip students and parents:

Students: $125
Adults: $215

Students/adults who are behind on payments will also have to turn in the late payments along with the final payment amount. Students who have a positive balance in their fundraiser account will owe less.

post_text:
PLEASE SHARE...

Attention Mobridge-Pollock 5th grade students:

It's time to clean your room and find your RECORDER! 5th grade music students will continue Recorder Karate this school year! Playing the recorder is a great way to learn to read music AND to help reinforce skills needed for band.

Please bring your recorder to school this week so we can get back in the swing of making awesome recorder music!

Make sure to write your name on the back side, near the bottom, with a permanent marker. You can bring it to Mrs. Zahn at the open house in the Upper Elementary on Monday night between 6:30 and 7:30 p.m., or bring it to school that week.

If you left your recorder in the music room in May, Mrs. Zahn already has it.

Can't find your recorder? Mrs. Zahn will have order forms to purchase a new one at a very small cost.

Welcome back to school...TOOT TOOT!

post_text:
PLEASE SHARE!

Attention Mobridge-Pollock 3rd, 4th, and 5th graders:

You are invited to join Tiger Music for the 2017-18 school year!

Tiger Music is an after-school choir that rehearses every Tuesday from 3:20 to 4:00 p.m., beginning September 5.

There is NO COST to join! The group performs at all 4th/5th grade concerts, community events, assisted living, nursing home, and....NEW this year.....we will perform the national anthem at MPHS athletic events!

You can sign up at the open house on Monday, August 21 between 6:30 and 7:30 p.m. Look for Mrs. Zahn in the Upper Elementary hallway!

ALL singers who sign up at the open house will be entered to win a PRIZE which will be given away at the winter concert.
